post_text:
From the Marlboro Educational Foundation:

Good evening Marlboro Neighbors,

Thank you for your recent Marlboro Strong Lawn Sign order! Signs are in the process of being produced, and we delivered the first 80 orders today. We will continue to deliver signs as the printer completes portions of our order. All signs will be delivered by the end of next week.

We appreciate your support and look forward to seeing signs all over town!

Sincerely,
The Trustees and Volunteers of the Marlboro Educational Foundation

post_text: Sunday Night MTPS Update (March 15, 2020)
text: Sunday Night MTPS Update (March 15, 2020)

post_text:
Hello Marlboro Community,

As you know, there is a massive concern in our district and in the world regarding COVID-19. As your superintendent, I take the safety and security of my students, staff, and community seriously. Regardless of any official announcement that has yet to come, I am making the decision to close our school district for the next two weeks for the safety of our entire community. The Marlboro Township School District will be closed from March 16th through March 27th.

The following is a plan for how we will utilize these days:

Monday, March 16th will be considered one of our inclement weather days. In other words, it will be treated just like a snow day. There will be no expectation of students to complete any type of work on this day.

Tuesday, March 17th through Friday, March 27th will be remote learning days.

Expect a detailed communication to follow later today.

Sincerely,

Eric

Dr. Eric M. Hibbs
text:
Hello Marlboro Community,

As you know, there is a massive concern in our district and in the world regarding COVID-19. As your superintendent, I take the safety and security of my students, staff, and community seriously. Regardless of any official announcement that has yet to come, I am making the decision to close our school district for the next two weeks for the safety of our entire community. The Marlboro Township School District will be closed from March 16th through March 27th.

The following is a plan for how we will utilize these days:

Monday, March 16th will be considered one of our inclement weather days. In other words, it will be treated just like a snow day. There will be no expectation of students to complete any type of work on this day.

Tuesday, March 17th through Friday, March 27th will be remote learning days.

Expect a detailed communication to follow later today.

Sincerely,

Eric

Dr. Eric M. Hibbs
